1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,680
{\an8}Mom, I'm sorry…

2
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
{\an8}…that I wasn't upfront with you.

3
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,479
{\an8}I was afraid that if I told you,

4
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,640
{\an8}your condition would get worse.

5
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,680
{\an8}Who taught you to say that?

6
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:14,880
{\an8}But it's true!

7
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,560
{\an8}You and Dad always fight
whenever you meet.

8
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,560
{\an8}You're so heartless!

9
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,240
{\an8}I hate you, Mom!

10
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:27,800
{\an8}Mook,

11
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:29,920
{\an8}do you remember?

12
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,440
{\an8}I asked you to have faith in my love.

13
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,960
{\an8}I've proven it to you, see?

14
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,840
My name is Anna Teerasu.

15
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:49,080
I am the CEO at TJ Group.

16
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,600
Oh dear.

17
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,120
I'm in the wrong seat, aren't I?

18
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,520
No worries. Please have a seat.

19
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,160
Then, let's get started.

20
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,040
I will be clear and concise.

21
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,920
This won't take long.

22
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:29,640
First, I'd like to inform you all
that going forward,

23
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,160
Mr. Theechuda Teerasu

24
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:36,360
will no longer have any involvement
whatsoever with TJ Group,

25
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:41,560
and he will lose all co-management rights
at Narin Beach Resort.

26
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,120
Second,

27
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,840
I am taking over management here
in his place.

28
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:57,760
I will have decision-making power
proportional to the number of my shares.

29
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:03,120
And lastly, there will be adjustments
to our corporate structure

30
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,400
and our management approach.

31
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:09,840
This is to ensure that Narin Beach Resort
meets our objectives.

32
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,760
What does all this mean?

33
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:20,519
It means that we're shuffling the cards
of our management planning

34
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:26,520
as well as our employee evaluations
where applicable.

35
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,440
Maybe it's nothing serious,
like we're afraid of.

36
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,440
I know my mom well.

37
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,440
She'd do anything to win against me.

38
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,440
She did it to you too, remember?

39
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:55,240
Can I ask you something?

40
00:04:56,160 --> 00:05:00,880
Up until now,
how is your relationship with her?

41
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:04,120
Since she adopted me
from Piamsuk Orphanage…

42
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,280
she has changed my name,

43
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,920
shaped me into this person
she wanted me to be,

44
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:17,280
sent me to good schools,
and taken good care of me.

45
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:22,280
But every time she gives me something,

46
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,480
she sets a condition.

47
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,760
And I have to do something
in return for it.

48
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,480
Something that's twice as great.

49
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,400
That's how I've always lived.

50
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,440
And another thing I remember is that…

51
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:46,240
I've never felt any love coming from her.

52
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:56,160
But Mr. Thee promised us
when we signed the contract

53
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,200
that there wouldn't be
any personnel changes.

54
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:05,520
Then, let me go back
and clarify the first point

55
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,480
that I mentioned earlier once again.

56
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,720
Going forward,

57
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:14,640
Mr. Thee will no longer have
any decision-making power whatsoever.

58
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,120
But Mr. Thee--

59
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:24,360
Does anyone else
have any questions or concerns?

60
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,760
If not, I'd like to end this meeting.

61
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,960
Since you're all silent,

62
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:39,040
I'll take it that you have no objections.

63
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,080
In that case, that concludes our meeting.

64
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,720
I must ask you all to leave

65
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,280
because I have a personal matter
to discuss with Ms. Narin.

66
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,360
I've heard about you and Thee.

67
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,520
What a small world we live in.

68
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,440
I'll be frank with you.

69
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,200
If you're going to pull
the "I'm his birth mother" card

70
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:39,240
to win Thee back from me,

71
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:42,080
I think you're making the wrong decision.

72
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:49,040
So you did all this because you're afraid
you'd lose Thee, didn't you?

73
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:55,280
I never planned to take him away from you.

74
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:58,960
In fact, I appreciate you
for raising him well,

75
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:02,600
and I think Thee is very lucky
to have a mother like you.

76
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:07,080
But he can only have one mother,

77
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,680
and everything should go back
to the way it was.

78
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:16,240
As for the changes to this place,
it depends on your decision now,

79
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,560
Ms. Narin.

80
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,799
I'm really sorry, Ms. Narin.

81
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,039
I never expected

82
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:43,480
that The One buying our shares
would cause all this trouble.

83
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,200
Mom!

84
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,680
Good afternoon.

85
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,400
"Mom"?

86
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,400
I'll tell you about it later,
Mr. Chadchai,

87
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,520
but now, I must ask you to leave.

88
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:00,960
Of course.

89
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,520
Have a seat, honey.

90
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,520
Mom, are you okay?

91
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,800
I'm okay.

92
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,600
What did my mother say?

93
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:22,880
Mrs. Anna said she's stripping you
of all your management rights

94
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:26,240
and replacing you as management here.

95
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:29,800
She'll also change
the hotel's entire system.

96
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,360
The One holds more shares than us,

97
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,960
which gives them
total decision-making power.

98
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:52,080
I'm sorry, Mom,
for causing all this trouble.

99
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,880
Don't apologize, honey.

100
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:59,880
I know that Mrs. Anna's only doing this
because she doesn't want to lose you.

101
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:06,240
But I'm not an object
for her to use me as leverage like this.

102
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:11,680
If I need to lose something
in order to see my son again,

103
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:12,960
I'll gladly oblige.

104
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:47,120
I assume you've told Thee
about the shareholder meeting

105
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,480
- that I called today.
- Yes.

106
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:52,960
Good,

107
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:57,880
because I want him to know
what will happen to his loved ones

108
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,560
if he dares to cross me.

109
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:03,240
Don't you feel sorry
for him at all, Mrs. Anna?

110
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,480
Well, he never cared about my feelings.

111
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:13,040
I'll wait and see how he'll handle this.

112
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:16,000
But he's still your son, no matter what.

113
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:19,640
I hope you don't forget that.

114
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:41,120
Why can't I have a baby?

115
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,160
Why does it have to be me?

116
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,280
Please calm down.

117
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:53,040
I won't let John try for a baby
with another woman!

118
00:11:55,440 --> 00:12:01,360
I need a baby,
so I can secure everything that's mine.

119
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:09,360
Pitak, you have to help me!

120
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,960
Why don't you want to eat?

121
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,040
I want to go home.

122
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,200
You mean the orphanage?

123
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:42,040
You want to go back
to being an orphan again?

124
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,800
I have a mother.

125
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,400
I'm going back there to find her.

126
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,080
I am your mother.

127
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,120
You're not!

128
00:13:56,760 --> 00:14:01,560
Remember, from now on, I'm your mother.

129
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,520
And Mr. John is your father.

130
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,760
You have to do everything I tell you,

131
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:10,160
or I'll stop donating to Piamsuk Orphanage

132
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:13,120
and your friends will be in trouble.

133
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,400
Understood?

134
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:24,120
So, if I do everything you say,
I'll get to go back to my mom, right?

135
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,640
You'll get everything you want.

136
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:33,640
Now, call me "mother".

137
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,560
Mother.

138
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:17,120
MUSCLE CAR THAILAND

139
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:32,520
{\an8}BANGKOK FASHION CONTEST 2022 - BELLA BELL
THE BEST OF YOUNG DESIGNERS

140
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:38,680
{\an8}This is an award Ms. Bell won
from a contest for designers.

141
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:42,680
I think the person
she wants to show it off to the most

142
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:44,240
is you.

143
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:50,920
Ms. Bell's worked hard to prove herself
so that you'd see her worth.

144
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:56,600
That's more important to Ms. Bell
than the award itself.

145
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:53,680
Lately, you never have time
for your employees, Boss.

146
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:58,840
I need to tell you something important.

147
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:04,480
Prao and I have decided to get a divorce.

148
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,000
And she's okay with it?

149
00:21:09,920 --> 00:21:12,080
She was the one who decided.

150
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:17,560
I think we've come to a point
where she's accepted the truth

151
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:20,800
that we both can't be
what we want each other to be,

152
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,000
and we can no longer force ourselves.

153
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:32,440
Talking things out and accepting the truth
are the best idea.

154
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,400
You might view it as a failure,

155
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:42,480
but to me, it might be a new beginning
that's better than the last.

156
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,840
Prao and I agreed that

157
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:54,000
it'll be better for Poonpun this way.

158
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:59,000
But we'll still be good parents to him.

159
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,880
Well, does Bella know about this yet?

160
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,520
My mom lets me eat pizza now, Kongkwan.

161
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,880
- Really?
- Yeah.

162
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:17,040
And she stopped fighting with my dad too.

163
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,160
My mom and dad said they'd become friends.

164
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:21,600
And since they're friends,
they won't fight.

165
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:24,160
Just like my mom and dad used to say.

166
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:31,120
So that means
they'll stop being my parents?

167
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,960
No, they still are.

168
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:36,160
It's just that they'll be friends instead.

169
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:40,880
It's actually great. This way,
they won't fight like they used to.

170
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:46,640
And it means I'll get to eat pizza again
and mom won't scold me, right?

171
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,640
Let's go.

172
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,280
Can you send them this bid proposal?

173
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:01,880
Sure, Ms. Usa.

174
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:05,240
Did you tell accounting about my orders?

175
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,280
Yes, I did.

176
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:30,320
Do I really have to handle all this?

177
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:34,440
This isn't even half
of what Mr. Thee used to handle.

178
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:41,920
Come on in.

179
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,600
Someone's here to see you, Mrs. Anna.

180
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:51,160
Who? Can't you see I'm busy?

181
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,840
It's Mr. Joe, ma'am.

182
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,480
I wanted to see you today

183
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:19,760
because I need to tell you
something important.

184
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:25,160
So you've changed your mind and decided
to sign our project's contract?

185
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,760
I must apologize on Thee's behalf.

186
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:36,720
I haven't been ignoring this issue either.

187
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:40,840
Recently, I've stripped him

188
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:43,240
of all his management rights
over TJ Group.

189
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,760
I've decided

190
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,760
to invest with you
like I planned to at first.

191
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:58,280
I knew I wasn't wrong about you.

192
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:00,640
You're a visionary.

193
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:05,160
You can separate work
and personal life very well.

194
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:09,040
But I have one condition.

195
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:12,320
What's the condition?

196
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:20,600
I'll only sign the project's contract
if Mr. Thee is in charge of this project.

197
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,200
Excuse me?

198
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:26,920
Aren't you mad at Thee?

199
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,920
You said it yourself.

200
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:35,520
I can separate work and personal life.

201
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:41,400
And I don't see anyone
who's capable enough

202
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,880
that I can trust as much as Thee.

203
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:51,120
I'll leave it to you to decide.

204
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:54,320
- If you'll excuse me.
- Yes.

205
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,400
See you later.

206
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:21,720
What's going on? You sure went all out.

207
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:31,600
Well, it's a special day, after all.

208
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,880
What's the occasion?

209
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:50,600
It's what I wanted to do for you.

210
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:53,400
It just wasn't the right time back then.

211
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,680
So you…

212
00:26:58,600 --> 00:26:59,760
Prao and I

213
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:02,880
got a divorce.

214
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:13,840
I HEREBY CERTIFY THAT THE INFORMATION
PROVIDED IS TRUE AND CORRECT

215
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:24,320
HUSBAND'S SIGNATURE - WIFE'S SIGNATURE

216
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:32,880
Thank you.

217
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:37,280
You're all set.

218
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,200
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

219
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:52,440
We can still be good friends, right, Prao?

220
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:55,520
Of course.

221
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:59,200
If your to-be-girlfriend
won't get jealous, then sure.

222
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:05,680
I promise that I'll do my best
as a father like always.

223
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:07,720
Of course you will.

224
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:10,760
Once you become a parent,
you're always a parent.

225
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:18,160
I won't mind it
if you want to start over with someone.

226
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,760
You can go ahead and move on.

227
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:40,080
<i>We talked,</i>

228
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,400
and we settled things on good terms.

229
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,560
It didn't happen because of you at all.

230
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,640
Actually, I'd been considering it
for a while.

231
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:56,760
If I didn't know you and Mr. Thee,

232
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,000
I wouldn't be where I am today.

233
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,080
Me and Thee?

234
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:06,560
Yes.

235
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:12,440
Mr. Thee gave me the courage
to accept the truth.

236
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:19,800
And you gave me the courage
to walk out of my comfort zone.

237
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:25,760
I used to tell myself

238
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:29,880
I wouldn't be able to love anyone again.

239
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:47,920
But you let me experience it once again.

240
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:55,320
Can you give me a chance?

241
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:18,000
How's that for your answer?

242
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,080
Sure.

243
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:12,720
Can you read that?
It's pronounced "confused".

244
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,280
- With a "C"?
- Want to talk about anything else?

245
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:22,240
‪Mom, let me help.

246
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:25,680
Looks like he'll be stuck here now.

247
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:29,320
Kongkwan asks about Mr. Thee every day.

248
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:39,040
What are you and Mr. Thee going to do now?

249
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,760
Or do you want me to ask him myself?

250
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:50,960
Mom! Stop teasing me.

251
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:56,720
I think it's nice
to take things slow like this.

252
00:31:57,880 --> 00:32:01,800
After all, he's got a lot
to think about and to deal with,

253
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,640
like the situation with Mrs. Anna.

254
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:10,280
When he didn't have a mother,
it was a problem.

255
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:13,600
Yet, now that he has two mothers,
there's still a problem.

256
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:19,640
But I think both his mothers
love him just the same.

257
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:23,000
It's just that their ways
of showing love are different.

258
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,520
Is Kongkwan asleep?

259
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:50,680
Yes.

260
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:55,120
Thank you for staying
and keeping her company.

261
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,880
Actually, she's the one
who kept me company.

262
00:32:58,960 --> 00:32:59,800
I had lots of fun.

263
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:07,840
Did you hear about my boss and Mrs. Prao?

264
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:12,120
They got a divorce.

265
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:16,840
They ended things on good terms,
and they agreed to remain good friends.

266
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:23,600
As far as I know,
Mr. Pat's a pretty good guy.

267
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:26,200
I'm sure he knows by now

268
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:30,520
what he really wants,
so he wanted to make things clear.

269
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,320
So…

270
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:39,240
what about us?

271
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:44,120
Aren't you stressed enough
about the current situation?

272
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:49,240
Not to mention Mrs. Anna.

273
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:00,000
Hello, Mr. Pitak.

274
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:06,120
Sure. I'll go tomorrow.

275
00:34:14,639 --> 00:34:18,239
Looks like we really have to choose
an auspicious date for our wedding now.

276
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:36,520
Have a seat.

277
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:48,199
If I hadn't called you,
you never would've come, would you?

278
00:34:49,199 --> 00:34:51,199
Well, I thought you didn't want to see me.

279
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:55,520
Even when you had a shareholder meeting
at Narin Beach Resort,

280
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:57,600
you didn't tell me anything.

281
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,840
So, why did you want to see me today?

282
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:11,320
Mr. Joe agreed to sign
the project's contract with us…

283
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,840
with TJ Group.

284
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,040
Congratulations.

285
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:28,160
But Mr. Joe has a condition, Mr. Thee.

286
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,480
What's the condition?

287
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,760
You need to be in charge of the project.

288
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:45,080
About how I'm calling off the wedding too.

289
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:49,800
My daughter wasn't sad
that you refused to marry her at all.

290
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:54,400
I actually invited you here today
to ask you something.

291
00:35:55,160 --> 00:35:59,560
Do you happen to know the man named Anapat
who's friends with my daughter?

292
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:01,160
Who is he? What's his background?

293
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:06,640
Mr. Anapat is the CEO
of A Round Trip Travel.

294
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:07,800
They're The One's partner.

295
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:13,760
He's polite, and he's always been
very responsible in his work.

296
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:20,560
How are things between you and Mrs. Anna?

297
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:24,720
I heard she stripped you
of your role at TJ Group?

298
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,960
She's very mad at me,

299
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:33,360
but I do understand
and accept all of her decisions.

300
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:41,400
Mr. Joe, as for the project
you wanted to invest with us--

301
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:42,720
Right,

302
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:44,800
I wanted to talk to you about it too.

303
00:36:46,240 --> 00:36:47,760
I've made my decision.

304
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,800
I'd like to invest with you,

305
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:54,440
but on the condition
that you must be in charge of the project.

306
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:59,480
But I don't think my mom will allow it.

307
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,600
I know Mrs. Anna well.

308
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,840
She always chooses the best option.

309
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,320
I'm no different.

310
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:11,080
Investing in something
with unpredictable risks

311
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,840
is something I'd never do.

312
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:25,320
So you want me to go back
to being in charge of the project?

313
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,280
You were the one who taught me

314
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:40,520
that no matter what I plan to do,
I need to get something in return.

315
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,800
Tell me what you need.

316
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:51,960
I'd like to buy
all of Narin Beach Resort's shares back

317
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:52,960
from The One.

318
00:38:30,080 --> 00:38:31,680
Hi. You're here already?

319
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:34,360
Let me finish my work really quick.

320
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:05,840
Dad!

321
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:13,760
Congratulations.

322
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,200
But next time,

323
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,520
you have to come show off
your awards to me, okay?

324
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:14,840
- Thee.
- Let me help you, Mom.

325
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,400
Sure. Thanks, honey.

326
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:21,000
The other day, I really enjoyed
Mrs. Aree's banana in coconut milk,

327
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:22,480
so I asked for her recipe.

328
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:24,760
You two try it and tell me if it's good.

329
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:25,800
Sure.

330
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:32,240
Before we eat our desserts,
I have good news to share with you today.

331
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,040
You got all your shares back.

332
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:41,760
Now, you're the only rightful owner
of Narin Beach Resort.

333
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,840
What do you mean?

334
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:48,520
I bought back
all of TJ Group's shares for you.

335
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:51,800
Really, honey?

336
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:55,760
Yes, Mom.

337
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:59,800
In return, I'll be in charge
of the project my mother is about to do.

338
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:03,160
That's good, honey.

339
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:05,800
You have to help Mrs. Anna
in every way you can.

340
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,800
I have something to tell you too.

341
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:14,360
Mook, come sit next to me.

342
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,440
Okay.

343
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:29,920
I'm handing Narin Beach Resort over
to you, Saifah.

344
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,120
Why, Mom?

345
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:39,440
I've been working hard for this day,

346
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:42,240
the day I get to meet my son

347
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:46,120
and hand everything over to him.

348
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:50,400
Plus, I want to rest now.

349
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:53,880
What about you two?

350
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:56,680
What are your plans for the future?

351
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:58,720
See?

352
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,600
We really have to set a date
for our wedding now.

353
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:13,760
I hope you'll stay by each other's side

354
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:16,560
and take care of each other
as best you can.

355
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,520
Please take care of Saifah, Mook.

356
00:42:22,120 --> 00:42:23,000
Of course.

357
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,200
So the bid results aren't out yet?

358
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:50,760
Ms. Usa is the coordinator for that,

359
00:42:50,840 --> 00:42:53,800
so any updates should go through her.

360
00:42:58,960 --> 00:43:02,200
USA - CALLING…

361
00:43:14,160 --> 00:43:15,000
Come on in.

362
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:20,440
Mr. Apichart, the company we bid for

363
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:25,120
contacted us, asking us to clarify
the document forgery claims

364
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,600
made by one of our competitors.

365
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,280
Call Ms. Usa.

366
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:34,440
She hasn't come into work yet.

367
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:36,400
I last saw her yesterday.

368
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:40,120
She came into work for a bit,
then she left and went somewhere.

369
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:55,160
Oh no!

370
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:01,200
Why is it such a mess in here?

371
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,760
Doesn't his girlfriend
take care of anything?

372
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:13,080
What a mess.

373
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:35,040
Yes, Kuk?

374
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:52,160
FAMILY TOUR AND TRAVEL

375
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,680
What happened, Kuk?

376
00:44:56,840 --> 00:44:59,480
Tell me! What happened?

377
00:45:00,880 --> 00:45:04,280
Ma. Ma, you have to help me.

378
00:45:04,360 --> 00:45:07,360
{\an8}The company we bid for
wants to investigate us

379
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:09,960
over claims that we forged our documents.

380
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:12,680
What do we do now, Ma?

381
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:16,560
{\an8}But Usa said we had it in the bag!

382
00:45:16,640 --> 00:45:19,800
{\an8}She also said Anna
would be able to help us.

383
00:45:20,880 --> 00:45:22,480
So, where is she?

384
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:24,360
Why isn't she helping you deal with this?

385
00:45:26,360 --> 00:45:27,440
I don't know, Ma.

386
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:29,040
I don't know where she went.

387
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:33,160
I can't get a hold of Ms. Usa.

388
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:36,400
And the people in accounting
told me that, earlier,

389
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:39,200
she ordered that 5,000,000 baht
be sent to her from our account,

390
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:41,640
claiming she'd use it for the bid.

391
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:44,600
What? What'd you say? Five million?!

392
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:46,120
Why am I just hearing about this now?

393
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:53,280
So that means she…

394
00:45:54,240 --> 00:45:57,520
Ma, Ma, Ma. Sit.

395
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:59,160
Sit down.

396
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:00,920
Get me an inhaler.

397
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,040
Got it.

398
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:05,480
Ma. You have to help me, Ma.

399
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:07,280
You have to help me.

400
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:11,360
No wonder why, in your room,

401
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:14,080
all of her clothes
and belongings are gone.

402
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:17,000
She must've run away already.

403
00:46:20,040 --> 00:46:22,360
Ma, you have to help me.

404
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:24,080
I don't want to go to jail, Ma.

405
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:25,640
What should I do, Ma?

406
00:46:25,720 --> 00:46:28,480
Ma! You have to help me, Ma.

407
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:30,320
Ma, you have to help me.

408
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:33,280
- Ma!
- Mrs. Anna.

409
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:37,800
Mrs. Anna should be able to help us.

410
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:44,320
Are you sure, Ma?

411
00:46:46,720 --> 00:46:48,800
I don't want to go to jail, Ma.

412
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:53,040
I don't want to.

413
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,720
I don't want to go to jail.

414
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:56,720
I don't want to go to jail.

415
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,280
We did everything as you suggested.

416
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:05,880
You've got to help my son, Mrs. Anna.

417
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:10,800
What? I never suggested you
to forge your documents.

418
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:13,640
Why didn't you come to me
before doing those things?

419
00:47:14,280 --> 00:47:17,840
Over at the company
I recommended you, they're furious.

420
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:21,880
They told me someone reported
that your company rigged the bid

421
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:24,160
and that you don't match
their qualifications.

422
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:27,160
But Usa told me
you'd help our company win the bid.

423
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:28,680
That's irrelevant.

424
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:33,080
I said I could put in a good word
for your company,

425
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:36,160
and you'd have to submit
your bid normally.

426
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:40,320
I never told you to forge documents
or play dirty like that.

427
00:47:42,840 --> 00:47:46,120
Can you please find a way
to help my son, Mrs. Anna?

428
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:48,640
I can't promise that I'll be able to help,

429
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:51,800
because what you did really was wrong.

430
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:56,920
Ma. You have to help me, Ma.

431
00:48:10,240 --> 00:48:11,360
Please, Ma.

432
00:48:11,440 --> 00:48:13,640
It's okay, honey. You're okay. Relax.

433
00:48:31,360 --> 00:48:32,240
Ma.

434
00:48:36,080 --> 00:48:39,360
Ma, will they tell the police
to arrest me?

435
00:48:40,160 --> 00:48:42,920
Or should we tell them
I had no idea about it

436
00:48:43,520 --> 00:48:45,400
and Usa was the one who did everything?

437
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:47,760
I've got nothing to do with it, Ma. Ma!

438
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:51,120
I know, I know, I know!

439
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:54,160
Of course I'd have to find
a way to help you.

440
00:48:54,240 --> 00:48:57,640
But right now, my head
feels like it's about to burst.

441
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:01,960
Let's think of a new plan tomorrow, Kuk.

442
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:14,840
What do I do?

443
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:22,520
I've given them the envelope.

444
00:49:22,600 --> 00:49:25,600
What if we get caught
rigging the bid with Mr. Somkiat?

445
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:27,760
Don't be afraid of such nonsense, Kuk.

446
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:31,320
I told you, Mrs. Anna
will fully support us.

447
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:33,960
All we need to do is win the bid.

448
00:49:34,880 --> 00:49:37,960
I'll help you any way I can.

449
00:49:38,040 --> 00:49:40,680
I won't leave you like Mook did.

450
00:49:43,560 --> 00:49:47,640
- Oh no!
- Ma! Ma!

451
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:54,560
Kuk!

452
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:58,720
- Help!
- Ma, what happened?

453
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:01,440
I'm screwed! Help!

454
00:50:02,480 --> 00:50:03,840
It's all gone.

455
00:50:04,440 --> 00:50:06,000
My stuff…

456
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,160
She took it all.

457
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:37,080
I went easy on you, you old hag.

458
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:38,600
That's what you get for being stingy.

459
00:50:40,920 --> 00:50:42,080
Serves you right.

460
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:45,360
You lost the bid,
and your company lost its reputation.

461
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:53,600
As for all this stuff
and the 5,000,000 baht,

462
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:56,160
just think of them as my bonus,

463
00:50:56,680 --> 00:50:57,840
you mama's boy.

464
00:51:08,120 --> 00:51:10,280
CASHIER'S CHEQUE
USA PATTARASIN - ONE MILLION BAHT

465
00:51:13,680 --> 00:51:18,640
Thank you, Mr. Somkiat,
for trusting me with this partnership.

466
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:21,320
I'm the one who should thank you, Ms. Usa.

467
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:24,280
Our company can't lose this bid.

468
00:51:26,520 --> 00:51:28,960
And Family Tour is a tough competitor.

469
00:51:29,560 --> 00:51:32,560
I just want to ensure
my company won't lose the bid.

470
00:51:34,600 --> 00:51:36,600
Don't worry, Mr. Somkiat.

471
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:40,240
I'm in charge of all the paperwork
for the bid.

472
00:51:40,320 --> 00:51:41,680
I assure you,

473
00:51:41,760 --> 00:51:47,320
the numbers we propose for the bid
will be exactly what you want for sure.

474
00:51:49,680 --> 00:51:51,640
You're quite smart, Ms. Usa.

475
00:51:52,240 --> 00:51:54,720
Let me know if you ever want
to find a new place to work.

476
00:51:56,320 --> 00:51:59,440
I'll accept every offer you give me.

477
00:52:00,680 --> 00:52:01,800
Really?

478
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:05,160
I just so happened
to be seeking new experiences.

479
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,480
In that case,

480
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:12,840
I'll give you another important
piece of information.

481
00:52:15,640 --> 00:52:17,280
The truth is,

482
00:52:17,360 --> 00:52:20,000
Family Tour doesn't meet
all the qualifications

483
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:23,800
like we claimed in the bid proposal.

484
00:52:23,880 --> 00:52:28,200
So that means
there have been forgeries in the proposal?

485
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:03,640
‪Let me see?

486
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:12,560
I think it's a great idea, Whan.

487
00:53:12,640 --> 00:53:15,360
- Okay.
- Organizing a trip with an itinerary,

488
00:53:15,440 --> 00:53:16,840
- document preparation,
- Look.

489
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:20,640
and travel advisory for each country
can help reassure our clients.

490
00:53:20,720 --> 00:53:21,680
Okay.

491
00:53:22,840 --> 00:53:25,640
Don't forget to post
all this information on our page,

492
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:28,840
so that when people share it,
it'll also promote our company.

493
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:29,800
Sure.

494
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:32,840
I'll create an artwork
and send it over for you to check.

495
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:34,400
Okay. Go ahead.

496
00:53:35,000 --> 00:53:35,840
‪Let's zoom in.

497
00:53:39,680 --> 00:53:41,800
Well, when are you two getting married?

498
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:43,320
- What?
- What?

499
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:46,080
I asked you when you two
are getting married.

500
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:48,000
You just won't stop being lovey-dovey.

501
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:50,960
What?

502
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:53,800
We're still in the talking stage.

503
00:53:53,880 --> 00:53:54,880
Don't say that.

504
00:53:54,960 --> 00:53:57,960
Oh, yeah? I just want to throw
my notebook at you.

505
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:04,680
- You can't go in there!
- Won't you keep watching the video?

506
00:54:04,760 --> 00:54:06,040
- No!
- Ma!

507
00:54:06,120 --> 00:54:08,200
Mr. Suetrong, call the police.

508
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:10,560
- Call them. Do it now.
- Got it.

509
00:54:10,640 --> 00:54:11,880
Now, please.

510
00:54:11,960 --> 00:54:13,960
- Hey, hey!
- Ma, what are you doing? Get up.

511
00:54:14,040 --> 00:54:15,040
Please don't do this.

512
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:17,040
Please help Kuk.

513
00:54:18,400 --> 00:54:19,800
I beg of you.

514
00:54:20,440 --> 00:54:22,560
Please help him, Mook.

515
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:24,800
Ma?

516
00:54:32,960 --> 00:54:34,000
Ma.

517
00:54:56,040 --> 00:54:58,800
Congratulations on being back to work.

518
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:03,760
I'm just back
to oversee Mr. Joe's project.

519
00:55:04,280 --> 00:55:08,360
As for the other operations,
I doubt my mom would let me manage them.

520
00:55:13,080 --> 00:55:17,320
If I find no issues with the details here,
we can prepare for the signing right away.

521
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:18,840
Got it.

522
00:55:20,000 --> 00:55:22,640
Congratulations for meeting
your mother, Mr. Thee.

523
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:25,840
Thank you.

524
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:33,480
I'm sorry I never told you
about it before, Mr. Pitak.

525
00:55:35,960 --> 00:55:37,840
Now, it's all up to Mrs. Anna.

526
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:40,880
It may be hard to make her understand.

527
00:55:46,720 --> 00:55:47,920
Come on in.

528
00:55:52,080 --> 00:55:53,160
Mook.

529
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:01,920
I've heard my mother
talk about the bid before.

530
00:56:02,520 --> 00:56:05,200
Mr. Amnat, who's a friend of hers,
is hosting the bid.

531
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:06,280
Yes.

532
00:56:07,480 --> 00:56:10,680
Mrs. Anna recommended
the project to Ms. Usa.

533
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:14,800
No one can contact Usa.
She's probably gotten away.

534
00:56:15,440 --> 00:56:17,440
I think she's onto them.

535
00:56:20,440 --> 00:56:22,400
Is there any way you can help Kuk?

536
00:56:27,440 --> 00:56:29,400
I'll try talking to my mom.

537
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:34,640
I'm sorry for bothering you
with Kuk's problem.

538
00:56:37,680 --> 00:56:39,120
It's no bother, Mook.

539
00:56:40,280 --> 00:56:42,960
Mr. Apichart
is Kongkwan's father, after all.

540
00:56:47,160 --> 00:56:49,960
{\an8}You don't need to be a dragon.

541
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:54,040
{\an8}You being my son is good enough.

542
00:56:56,320 --> 00:56:58,640
{\an8}One thing I've never given Thee

543
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:05,240
{\an8}is the love and warmth that a mother
is supposed to give her child.

544
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:07,440
{\an8}So,

545
00:57:07,520 --> 00:57:13,160
{\an8}why don't we both compensate him
with what we never gave to him before?

546
00:57:13,240 --> 00:57:14,240
{\an8}What do you think?

547
00:57:14,320 --> 00:57:19,480
{\an8}If I want to marry Thee,
will you be okay with that?

548
00:57:19,560 --> 00:57:21,800
{\an8}If it's Thee, then sure.

549
00:57:22,320 --> 00:57:23,560
{\an8}Thank you, honey.

550
00:58:16,280 --> 00:58:18,480
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

